
[1]disport

   DISPORT, n. [dis and sport.] Play; sport; pastime; diversion;
   amusement; merriment.

   DISPORT, v.i. To play; to wanton; to move lightly and without
   restraint; to move in gayety; as lambs disporting on the mead..

   Where light disports in ever mingling dyes.

         DISPORT, v.t. To divert or amuse; as, he disports himself.
